; Per-axis velocity/acceleration blending (regression H1).
; With non-uniform axis limits, each move's vel/ini_maxvel/acc should be
; limited by the participating axes. Pure-Z, diagonal-XY, and full-XYZ moves
; must each yield a distinct blended limit in the reference (C++) canon.
G21 G90 G94 G17
G0 X0 Y0 Z5
G1 Z0 F600          ; pure Z (slow axis) — reference caps at Z limit
G1 X20 F600         ; pure X (fast axis)
G1 Y20 F600         ; pure Y
G1 X0 Y0 F1200      ; diagonal XY
G1 X30 Y15 Z-10 F1500 ; full XYZ, Z-dominated
G0 Z5
M2
